The paper deals with a mechanism design problem for sharing rewards among a group of agents, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism proposed in the paper involves eliciting and aggregating subjective opinions from the agents, which requires some form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social influence modeling (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the mechanism, which suggests that it may involve some data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper addresses issues of fairness and individual rationality, which are important topics in machine learning and decision making (cs.LG).
